Language name: KOLOKUMA IJO
Language number: 4150
Alternate names: North-Central Ijo
Classification: Niger-Kardofanian, Kwa
Comments: Kolokuma Ijo is spoken on the Nun branch of the 
Niger delta system in Rivers State, Nigeria. There are two 
level tones. Vowel harmony separates 'close' vowels /i, e, 
u, o/ from their more open counterparts; /a/ is neutral. 
Nasalized vowels preceding stops are pronounced with a 
consonantal nasal offset homorganic with the stop.
Sources: 

Williamson, K. 1965. A Grammar of the Kolokuma Dialect of 
Ijo. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge.